  "dcterms:title": "Hologram Holospaces — curated multi-app templates",
  "dcterms:description": "A holospace template is a content-addressed COMPOSITION (Law L1): a single κ that opens one holospace tab nesting several apps already wired together. Members are referenced by the app's own root κ — never copied (compose by reference). The OS frame mounts each member through the same launcher every app uses; the template is pure orchestration. gen-apps-catalog stamps each member's holo:appRoot from the app closure and refuses any member that is not a real app.",
